**Upper South and Lower South Lot Confusion**

Red Rocks operates multiple parking areas that serve different seating sections and ticket types. Upper South Lot provides closest access to reserved seating areas, while Lower South Lot serves general admission and more distant reserved sections. The difference matters because walking from Lower South to upper seating sections involves climbing approximately 200 vertical feet of stairs and ramps.

During my sound check preparations, I regularly see passengers dropped at Lower South who discover they need Upper South access for their specific seats. The walk between lots takes 15-20 minutes and involves significant uphill hiking at elevation. Passengers unprepared for this physical demand often arrive at their seats exhausted before shows even begin.

